An Ado-Ekiti Chief Magistrate Court on Wednesday ordered that a 40-year-old man, accused of allegedly raping two minors, be remanded in police custody. The Police Prosecutor, Insp. Johnson Okunade, told the court that the defendant, Mathew John, committed the offence on Feb.23 in Ado-Ekiti. He alleged that the defendant raped a 13-year-old and a 15-year-old. Okunade alleged that the defendant lured the two girls, who lived in the same neighborhood with him and raped them. Chief Magistrate Adesoji Adegboye, who did not take the plea of the defendant, adjourned the case until March 25 for mention. (NAN) Man remanded over alleged rape of 16-year-old daughter When teachers prey on their students Malicious damage of goods: Man, 20, arraigned